  <title>Integer Literals</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Integer Literals</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Literal INT values may be specified in decimal, hexadecimal or binary notation:</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; color:#000000;">12345</text><br/><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; color:#000000;">0x1234ABCD</text><br/><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; color:#000000;">0b010010101</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">&#32;</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Integer literals may have one of the following suffixes:</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="3" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Suffix</para>
        </td>
        <td>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">L or l</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Signed 32 bits integer </para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">U or u</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Unsigned integer </para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
